    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1862-11-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1862-11-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="495" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d495">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Corwin</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 61.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1862-11-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 26, 1862.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of October 27 (No. 34) has
                            been received. It presents, in a very brief, yet a very comprehensive
                            way, the political and military situation of Mexico.</p>
                <p>Under date of the 24th instant I addressed you a despatch, (No. 61,)
                            which was forwarded by the mail of yesterday, and for which you will
                            please to consider the present a substitute, the first of this number
                            having been cancelled.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thomas Corwin</hi>, Esq.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
